Since the Russia-Ukraine conflict began in March, only 12 Ukrainian refugees have resettled in the U.S. through the country's refugee program, in stark contrast to a U.S. pledge to accept up to 100,000 Ukrainian refugees. So, 12 out of 100,000 is nothing but a drop in the bucket. Credits: Editor: Yuan Xin Designer: Wang Shiqi Chief editor: Ge Jing Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)